    <fr:title text="Irreducible space">Irreducible space</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  A topological space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>irreducible</html:em> if it is not the union of two proper closed subspaces. More generally, we can talk about when a subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is irreducible.
</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
