        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>6</fr:month>
              <fr:day>7</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-W1VU/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>idem-comm-W1VU</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/idem-comm-W1VU/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Irreducible closed subsets of spectra">Irreducible closed subsets of spectra</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Under the isomorphism in <fr:link href="/idem-comm-HLDT/" title="Frame of opens of spectra" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-HLDT/" display-uri="idem-comm-HLDT" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-HLDT/" display-uri="idem-comm-HLDT" /></fr:link>, a closed subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_I]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex> corresponding to an ideal <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/topl-0001/" title="Irreducible space" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-0001/" display-uri="topl-0001" type="local">irreducible</fr:link> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> is a prime ideal.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>7</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>
    Suppose <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_I]]></fr:tex> is irreducible. If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p \wedge  q \in  I]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_I \subseteq  C_{p \wedge  q} = C_p \cup  C_q]]></fr:tex>. By irreducibility, either <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p\in  I]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  I]]></fr:tex>, which implies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> is a prime ideal. 
  </html:p>

  <html:p>
    On the other hand, suppose <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> is prime. If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_I]]></fr:tex> is not irreducible, then we can find ideals <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[J,K]]></fr:tex> that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_I \subseteq  C_J \cup  C_K = C_{J \cap  K}]]></fr:tex>, or equivalently <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[J \cap  K \subseteq  I]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[J \not \subseteq  I]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \not \subseteq  I]]></fr:tex>. This way, pick <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p\in  J-I]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  K-I]]></fr:tex>, we get <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p \wedge  q\in  I]]></fr:tex> but <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p \not \in  I]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\not \in  I]]></fr:tex>, contradictory. Hence, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_I]]></fr:tex> must be irreducible.
  </html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
